# LiveKit Migration Context

This project migrated from mediasoup to LiveKit for WebRTC media routing. Socket.IO is retained for non-media signaling (sketches, emotes, peer info).

## Architecture

### Media (LiveKit)
- `src/hooks/useLivekitRoom.js` — connects to LiveKit, generates per-tab session ID to avoid identity collisions across browser tabs
- Uses **locally-scoped cancellation** (not refs) to be immune to React Strict Mode double-mount
- `src/app/api/livekit/token/route.js` — Next.js API route that validates Supabase JWT, checks user_roles/collaborator_ids, returns LiveKit access token with role-based `canPublish`
- Token identity format: `{userId}-{tabSessionId}`, real userId stored in participant metadata
- Anonymous users (Supabase anonymous auth) get `canPublish: false, canSubscribe: true`

### Signaling (Socket.IO — kept for backward compat)
- `src/hooks/useSignalingSocket.js` — standalone socket.io-client connection, sets `window.socket` for p5.js sketch compatibility
- Events preserved: relay, mousePosition, peerInfo, savePeerData, serverTime, joinLobby/leaveLobby, emote, counts
- `server/index.js` — Express + Socket.IO server, relay messages scoped by stageId

### Multi-Camera Broadcasting (RealtimeContext)
- `src/components/RealtimeContext.js` — provides `room` (LiveKit), `socket` (Socket.IO), `broadcastStreams` map, `selectedStreamId`
- Context value: `{ room, socket, broadcastStreams, selectedStreamId, setSelectedStreamId }`
- Track naming: `video-broadcast-{featureId}` and `audio-broadcast-{featureId}` where featureId is the UUID from the features table
- `parseBroadcastTrackName()` is exported from RealtimeContext for use by BroadcastStreamControls
- `broadcastStreams` shape: `{ [streamId]: { video: MediaStream, audio: MediaStream, videoPublication: RemoteTrackPublication } }`
- Simulcast quality: `VideoQuality.HIGH` for selected stream, `VideoQuality.LOW` for inactive streams (~150kbps each)
- Only the selected stream's audio plays; inactive thumbnails use muted video elements
- No peer video/audio streams — lobby peer tracking was removed (lobby is disabled)

## Track Publishing (BroadcastStreamControls)
- Video: 3 Mbps max, 30fps, VP8 with simulcast (360p + 180p layers)
- Audio: 128 Kbps, dtx disabled, RED enabled — optimized for pro audio interfaces (Scarlett, etc.)
- Audio processing (echo cancellation, noise suppression, auto gain) is force-disabled
- Broadcaster selects a stream sink from features (type: "broadcastStream") before publishing
- Occupancy check: scans room.remoteParticipants for matching track names, shows warning if sink is in use

## Capture (useUserMedia.js)
- Raw `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia()` — NOT LiveKit's track creation APIs
- Video: 1280x720 ideal, 30fps ideal
- Audio: stereo (channelCount ideal 2), all processing disabled

